zephyr-ncs-buildsystem
======================

This repository is build-system orchestration only. No third-party source is
redistributed by this repository itself; the container image built from this
repository downloads and integrates the projects listed below at build time,
each under its own license. Built images and resulting firmware inherit a
mix of licenses and must be redistributed accordingly.


Third-party projects
--------------------

  Zephyr Project (RTOS)
    https://github.com/zephyrproject-rtos/zephyr
    License: Apache-2.0

  Zephyr SDK (toolchain bundle)
    https://github.com/zephyrproject-rtos/sdk-ng
    Includes GCC (GPL-3.0 with GCC Runtime Library Exception), binutils
    (GPL-3.0), newlib (various BSD-style), picolibc (BSD-3-Clause), and
    other components under their respective licenses.

  west (Zephyr meta-tool)
    https://github.com/zephyrproject-rtos/west
    License: Apache-2.0

  nRF Connect SDK (sdk-nrf)
    https://github.com/nrfconnect/sdk-nrf
    License: LicenseRef-Nordic-5-Clause, BSD-3-Clause

  sdk-zephyr (Nordic fork of Zephyr)
    https://github.com/nrfconnect/sdk-zephyr
    License: Apache-2.0

  MCUboot
    https://github.com/mcu-tools/mcuboot
    License: Apache-2.0

  nrfxlib (Nordic binary libraries)
    https://github.com/nrfconnect/sdk-nrfxlib
    License: LicenseRef-Nordic-5-Clause
    Use of the libraries is restricted to Nordic Semiconductor integrated
    circuits.

  Trusted Firmware-M (TF-M)
    https://www.trustedfirmware.org/projects/tf-m/
    License: BSD-3-Clause

  JFrog CLI
    https://github.com/jfrog/jfrog-cli
    License: Apache-2.0

  Ubuntu (base image)
    https://ubuntu.com/legal/intellectual-property-policy
    License: Various per package (GPL-2.0, LGPL, BSD, MIT, Apache-2.0, ...).


